TY  - JOUR
AU  - Silvestre, Joaquim
T1  - Ambiguities in the Sign of Excess Effective Demand by Firms
PY  - 1982
Y1  - 1982/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297293
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 49
IS  - 4
SP  - 645
EP  - 651
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Can we state that at a given Benassy Fixprice Allocation z* there is, say, excess effective demand for a commodity? It turns out that in productive economies there may be ambiguities in the sign of excess effective demand: different effective demand vectors with different signs, may be compatible with z*. We prove: (a) no ambiguity exists if intermediate goods are ruled out and if all firms in the long side of a market perceive binding constraints; (b) in any case one can always select a vector of effective demands yielding minimal sets of buyer's and seller's markets.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297293
ER  - 



