TY  - JOUR
AU  - Dasgupta, Partha
AU  - Gilbert, Richard J.
AU  - Stiglitz, Joseph E.
T1  - Invention and Innovation Under Alternative Market Structures: The Case of Natural Resources
PY  - 1982
Y1  - 1982/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297287
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 49
IS  - 4
SP  - 567
EP  - 582
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper examines the interactions between market structure and resource allocation over time when there is endogenous technical progress. The structures considered are a planned economy, pure monopoly, and competition with patent rights. In an efficient allocation the date of invention coincides with the date of innovation (the date at which technology is used). This is also true with a pure monopoly, but monopoly retards technical progress relative to the efficient level.Competition for patents rights to a new technology results in excessively rapid technical progress if the resource endowment of the economy is sufficiently large. Also, competition may lead to “sleeping patents” where invention strictly precedes the date of innovation.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297287
ER  - 



